<doc id="759137" wikidata="Q1369886" url="?curid=759137" title="Toshiro Nomura">
<text>is a Japanese astronomer and co-discoverer of 13 asteroids with astronomers Kōyō Kawanishi and Matsuo Sugano.

He is also an earth-science teacher of Nada jr/sr highschool. The main-belt asteroid 6559 Nomura is named in his honor.

